---
Stdout:
Usage: run [OPTIONS] SCHEMA [API_NAME]

  Run tests against an API using a specified SCHEMA.

  [Required] SCHEMA: Path to an OpenAPI (`.json`, `.yml`) or GraphQL SDL file,
  or a URL pointing to such specifications.

  [Optional] API_NAME: Identifier for uploading test data to Schemathesis.io.

Options:
  -w, --workers [auto|1-64]                 Sets the number of concurrent
                                            workers for testing. Auto-adjusts if
                                            'auto' is specified.  [default: 1]
  --dry-run                                 Simulates test execution without
                                            making any actual requests, useful
                                            for validating data generation.
  --experimental [openapi-3.1|schema-analysis|stateful-test-runner|stateful-only|coverage-phase]
                                            Enable experimental features.
  --fixups [fast_api|utf8_bom|all]          Applies compatibility adjustments
                                            like 'fast_api', 'utf8_bom'.

API validation options:
  -c, --checks [not_a_server_error|status_code_conformance|content_type_conformance|response_headers_conformance|response_schema_conformance|negative_data_rejection|ignored_auth|all]
                                            Specifies the validation checks to
                                            apply to API responses. Provide a
                                            comma-separated list of checks such
                                            as 'not_a_server_error,status_code_c
                                            onformance', etc. Default is
                                            'not_a_server_error'.  [default:
                                            not_a_server_error]
  --exclude-checks [not_a_server_error|status_code_conformance|content_type_conformance|response_headers_conformance|response_schema_conformance|negative_data_rejection|ignored_auth]
                                            Specifies the validation checks to
                                            skip during testing. Provide a
                                            comma-separated list of checks you
                                            wish to bypass.
  --max-response-time INTEGER RANGE         Sets a custom time limit for API
                                            response times. The test will fail
                                            if a response time exceeds this
                                            limit. Provide the time in
                                            milliseconds.  [x>=1]
  -x, --exitfirst                           Terminates the test suite
                                            immediately upon the first failure
                                            or error encountered.
  --max-failures INTEGER RANGE              Terminates the test suite after
                                            reaching a specified number of
                                            failures or errors.  [x>=1]

Loader options:
  --app TEXT                     Specifies the WSGI/ASGI application under test,
                                 provided as an importable Python path.
  --wait-for-schema FLOAT RANGE  Maximum duration, in seconds, to wait for the
                                 API schema to become available. Disabled by
                                 default.  [x>=1.0]
  --validate-schema BOOLEAN      Validates the input API schema. Set to 'true'
                                 to enable or 'false' to disable.  [default:
                                 False]

Network requests options:
  -b, --base-url TEXT              Provides the base URL of the API, required
                                   when schema is provided as a file.
  --request-timeout INTEGER RANGE  Sets a timeout limit, in milliseconds, for
                                   each network request during tests.  [x>=1]
  --request-proxy TEXT             Set the proxy for all network requests.
  --request-tls-verify TEXT        Configures TLS certificate verification for
                                   server requests. Can specify path to
                                   CA_BUNDLE for custom certs.  [default: true]
  --request-cert PATH              File path of unencrypted client certificate
                                   for authentication. The certificate can be
                                   bundled with a private key (e.g. PEM) or the
                                   private key can be provided with the
                                   --request-cert-key argument.
  --request-cert-key PATH          Specifies the file path of the private key
                                   for the client certificate.
  --rate-limit TEXT                Specifies a rate limit for test requests in
                                   '<limit>/<duration>' format. Example -
                                   `100/m` for 100 requests per minute.
  -H, --header TEXT                Adds a custom HTTP header to all API
                                   requests. Format: 'Header-Name: Value'.
  -a, --auth TEXT                  Provides the server authentication details in
                                   the 'USER:PASSWORD' format.
  -A, --auth-type [basic|digest]   Specifies the authentication method. Default
                                   is 'basic'.  [default: basic]

Filtering options:
  --include-path TEXT                Path to include in testing.
  --include-path-regex TEXT          Path pattern to include in testing.
  --exclude-path TEXT                Path to exclude from testing.
  --exclude-path-regex TEXT          Path pattern to exclude from testing.
  --include-method TEXT              Method to include in testing.
  --include-method-regex TEXT        Method pattern to include in testing.
  --exclude-method TEXT              Method to exclude from testing.
  --exclude-method-regex TEXT        Method pattern to exclude from testing.
  --include-name TEXT                Operation name to include in testing.
  --include-name-regex TEXT          Operation name pattern to include in
                                     testing.
  --exclude-name TEXT                Operation name to exclude from testing.
  --exclude-name-regex TEXT          Operation name pattern to exclude from
                                     testing.
  --include-tag TEXT                 Tag to include in testing.
  --include-tag-regex TEXT           Tag pattern to include in testing.
  --exclude-tag TEXT                 Tag to exclude from testing.
  --exclude-tag-regex TEXT           Tag pattern to exclude from testing.
  --include-operation-id TEXT        ID to include in testing.
  --include-operation-id-regex TEXT  ID pattern to include in testing.
  --exclude-operation-id TEXT        ID to exclude from testing.
  --exclude-operation-id-regex TEXT  ID pattern to exclude from testing.
  --include-by TEXT                  Include API operations by expression
  --exclude-by TEXT                  Exclude API operations by expression
  --exclude-deprecated               Exclude deprecated API operations from
                                     testing.

Output options:
  --junit-xml FILENAME                  Outputs a JUnit-XML style report at the
                                        specified file path.
  --cassette-path FILENAME              Saves the test outcomes in a VCR-
                                        compatible format.
  --cassette-format [vcr|har]           Format of the saved cassettes.
  --cassette-preserve-exact-body-bytes  Retains exact byte sequence of payloads
                                        in cassettes, encoded as base64.
  --code-sample-style [python|curl]     Selects the code sample style for
                                        reproducing failures.
  --sanitize-output BOOLEAN             Enable or disable automatic output
                                        sanitization to obscure sensitive data.
                                        [default: True]
  --output-truncate TEXT                Specifies whether to truncate schemas
                                        and responses in error messages.
                                        [default: true]
  --show-trace                          Displays complete traceback information
                                        for internal errors.
  --debug-output-file FILENAME          Saves debugging information in a JSONL
                                        format at the specified file path.

Data generation options:
  -D, --data-generation-method [positive|negative|all]
                                            Specifies the approach Schemathesis
                                            uses to generate test data. Use
                                            'positive' for valid data,
                                            'negative' for invalid data, or
                                            'all' for both. Default is
                                            'positive'.  [default: positive]
  --stateful [none|links]                   Enables or disables stateful
                                            testing.
  --generation-allow-x00 TEXT               Determines whether to allow the
                                            generation of `␀` bytes within
                                            strings.  [default: true]
  --generation-codec TEXT                   Specifies the codec used for
                                            generating strings.
  --generation-with-security-parameters TEXT
                                            Whether to generate security
                                            parameters.  [default: true]
  --generation-graphql-allow-null TEXT      Whether `null` values should be used
                                            for optional arguments in GraphQL
                                            queries.  [default: true]
  --contrib-unique-data                     Forces the generation of unique test
                                            cases.
  --contrib-openapi-formats-uuid            Enables support for the 'uuid'
                                            string format in OpenAPI.
  --contrib-openapi-fill-missing-examples   Enables generation of random
                                            examples for API operations that do
                                            not have explicit examples defined.
  -t, --target [response_time|all]          Guides input generation to values
                                            more likely to expose bugs via
                                            targeted property-based testing.

Open API options:
  --force-schema-version [20|30]  Forces the schema to be interpreted as a
                                  particular OpenAPI version.
  --set-query TEXT                OpenAPI: Override a specific query parameter
                                  by specifying 'parameter=value'
  --set-header TEXT               OpenAPI: Override a specific header parameter
                                  by specifying 'parameter=value'
  --set-cookie TEXT               OpenAPI: Override a specific cookie parameter
                                  by specifying 'parameter=value'
  --set-path TEXT                 OpenAPI: Override a specific path parameter by
                                  specifying 'parameter=value'

Hypothesis engine options:
  --hypothesis-database TEXT                Configures storage for examples
                                            discovered by Hypothesis. Use 'none'
                                            to disable, ':memory:' for temporary
                                            storage, or specify a file path for
                                            persistent storage.
  --hypothesis-deadline INTEGER RANGE       Sets a time limit for each test case
                                            generated by Hypothesis, in
                                            milliseconds. Exceeding this limit
                                            will cause the test to fail.
                                            [1<=x<=300000]
  --hypothesis-derandomize                  Enables deterministic mode in
                                            Hypothesis, which eliminates random
                                            variation between test runs.
  --hypothesis-max-examples INTEGER RANGE   Sets the cap on the number of
                                            examples generated by Hypothesis for
                                            each API method/path pair.  [x>=1]
  --hypothesis-phases [explicit|reuse|generate|target|shrink]
                                            Specifies which testing phases to
                                            execute.
  --hypothesis-no-phases [explicit|reuse|generate|target|shrink]
                                            Specifies which testing phases to
                                            exclude from execution.
  --hypothesis-report-multiple-bugs BOOLEAN
                                            If set, only the most easily
                                            reproducible exception will be
                                            reported when multiple issues are
                                            found.
  --hypothesis-seed INTEGER                 Sets a seed value for Hypothesis,
                                            ensuring reproducibility across test
                                            runs.
  --hypothesis-suppress-health-check [data_too_large|filter_too_much|too_slow|large_base_example|all]
                                            Disables specified health checks
                                            from Hypothesis like
                                            'data_too_large', 'filter_too_much',
                                            etc. Provide a comma-separated list
  --hypothesis-verbosity [quiet|normal|verbose|debug]
                                            Controls the verbosity level of
                                            Hypothesis output.

Schemathesis.io options:
  --report TEXT                     Specifies how the generated report should be
                                    handled. If used without an argument, the
                                    report data will automatically be uploaded
                                    to Schemathesis.io. If a file name is
                                    provided, the report will be stored in that
                                    file. The report data, consisting of a tar
                                    gz file with multiple JSON files, is subject
                                    to change.
  --schemathesis-io-token TEXT      Schemathesis.io authentication token.
  --schemathesis-io-url TEXT        Schemathesis.io base URL.
  --schemathesis-io-telemetry TEXT  Controls whether you send anonymized CLI
                                    usage data to Schemathesis.io along with
                                    your report.  [default: true]
  --hosts-file FILE                 Path to a file to store the Schemathesis.io
                                    auth configuration.

Global options:
  -v, --verbosity  Increase verbosity of the output.
  --no-color       Disable ANSI color escape codes.
  --force-color    Explicitly tells to enable ANSI color escape codes.
  -h, --help       Show this message and exit.
